~ "Input is performed using the `input` function, which returns the value entered by the user as a result"

~ "As a single argument, you can pass a read stream (out / in / err)"
input (in)

~ "If the read stream is `in` -- then you don't need to pass the stream:"
input ()

~ "Example of a greeting program:"
output "Enter you name: "
output "Hello, " (input ()) (~n)
